        "timestamp": "2023-02-24 17:21:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nJust for your consideration, it may be better to keep *.sh script files as before with execution permissions rather than the new 644, although I understand that permissions may be changed at build time in the Dockerfile or being invoked through a shell for the entrypoint or directly.   For *.Dockerfile makes all sense the change to 644 you did.",
