          "username": "aravind.est"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2023-02-24 17:44:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> \n> Just for your consideration, it may be better to keep *.sh script files as before with execution permissions rather than the new 644, although I understand that permissions may be changed at build time in the Dockerfile or being invoked through a shell for the entrypoint or directly.   For *.Dockerfile makes all sense the change to 644 you did.\n\nYeah, It is better to have 755 for the executable file to show that it is a executable. However, this permission has no impact on the file's behavior in a Docker container.\n\nI have changed the *.sh files in order to align with other *.sh in the folder. Do you suggest to change all the *.sh files to have 755 ?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
